# Normalise line endings. This project is deployed to Linux (LXC), so keep LF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary-ish data files: leave untouched
*.db binary

# --- Deploy artifact (`git archive`, see scripts/make-dist.sh) ---------------
# `git archive` only takes tracked files anyway (.git/.venv/__pycache__ etc. drop
# out automatically). Additionally strip everything internal/dev-specific here, so
# the tarball only contains the files needed to install/operate: install.sh,
# pyproject.toml, app/**, deploy/**. Keep this list in sync with the installer.
#
# Docs in the release: ONLY the HTML user manuals (app/web/manual.html +
# handbuch.html, behind the ?-icon in the web UI, standalone-capable). README and
# CHANGELOG are developer/detail docs and are deliberately NOT shipped. The build
# (scripts/make-dist.sh) only reads app/__init__.py — the README is NOT needed.
README.md       export-ignore
README.de.md    export-ignore
Screenshots/    export-ignore
CHANGELOG.md    export-ignore
SECURITY.md     export-ignore
.github/        export-ignore
docs/           export-ignore
tests/          export-ignore
snmpdata/       export-ignore
scripts/        export-ignore
.gitattributes  export-ignore
.gitignore      export-ignore
